title: England wicket-keeper Sarah Taylor looking forward to chance to make... - Barryanddistrictnews.co.uk
text:
England's Sarah Taylor is "nervous and excited" about the prospect of becoming the first woman to play 'A' grade cricket in Australia. Taylor, 26, has been playing with women's side SA Scorpions and has impressed enough with her wicket-keeping and batting to earn a call for Northern Districts' first two-day game of the season against Port Adelaide this weekend.
 Barryanddistrictnews.co.uk.
